ameMeanings":[{"name":"Wood","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: mainly a topographic name for someone who lived in or by a wood, from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘wood’ (Old English <i>wudu</i>). In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, such as French   Bois   and Polish   Les  .","English: in a few cases, a nickname for an eccentric or perhaps a violent person, from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘frenzied, wild’ (Old English <i>wōd</i>).","Americanized form of French   Gadbois  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Woode","meanings":["(2007: 216; 2010: NA)","English: variant of   Wood  . — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau for this surname in the year 2000 is as high as 312, while the figure for 2010 is supposedly lower than 100."]},{"name":"Bois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide, Antoine, Donat, Marcel, Ovide, Ovila, Raoul, Serge.","French: topographic name for someone living or working in a wood, from (Old) French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (from Late Latin <i>boscum</i> ‘bush, shrub, undergrowth’, of ancient Germanic origin), or a habitational name from (Le) Bois, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Debois   and the most frequent French form   Dubois  . Compare also   Boie  ,   Boies  , and   Boyce  .","English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  ."]},{"name":"Woods","meanings":["English: variant of   Wood   with plural or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Irish: adopted as a translation of <b>Ó Cuill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Coll</i>’ (see   Quill  ), or in Ulster of <b>Mac Con Coille</b> ‘son of <i>Cú Choille</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘hound of the wood’, which has also been mistranslated   Cox  , as if formed with <i>coileach</i> ‘cock, rooster’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Wood VI was born in 1425, in North Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Wood, was 25 and his mother, Ann Pollard, was 21. He married Thomasine Crese about 1452, in North Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1469, in his hometown, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1425–1469":"1425–1469","1430–1476":"1430–1476","1431–1476":"1431–1476","1430–Female":"1430–Surnud","1460–1493":"1460–1493","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1404–1485":"1404–1485","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","circa 1452":"umbes 1452","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","1400":"1400","1476":"1476","1431":"1431","1485":"1485","1430":"1430","North Tawton, Devonshire, England":"North Tawton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1425–1469":"1425–1469","1430–1476":"1430–1476","1431–1476":"1431–1476","1430–Female":"1430–Kuollut","1460–1493":"1460–1493","1462–1522":"1462–1522","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1404–1485":"1404–1485","1462":"1462","1460":"1460","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","circa 1452":"noin 1452","1469":"1469","1522":"1522","1400":"1400","1476":"1476","1431":"1431","1485":"1485","1430":"1430","North Tawton, Devonshire, England":"North Tawton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Collingtree, Northamptonshire, England":"Collingtree, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1425–1469":"1425–1469","1430–1476":"1430–1476","1431–1476":"1431–1476","1430